WEBVTT

00:06.600 --> 00:07.960
[knocks on door]

00:08.000 --> 00:18.000
সাইট খুঁজে না পেলে ব্রাউজারে লিখুন:
-=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

00:08.040 --> 00:09.120
[Order] May I come in, sir?

00:10.000 --> 00:12.200
- [knocking continues]
- Your Honour?

00:12.280 --> 00:14.040
Don't just stand there, come inside!

00:15.800 --> 00:18.920
- Sir, I need your signature.
- What is this?

00:34.960 --> 00:37.080
- Thank you, sir.
- Hey, hey!

00:37.160 --> 00:39.040
Uh, sorry, sir. Sorry.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.760
Thank you. Thank you.

00:41.840 --> 00:43.560
[Mintu] Order. He's gone to see Mr Ghosh.

00:45.440 --> 00:46.600
- Oh, he's here.
- He's here.

00:46.680 --> 00:47.760
Did we get the approval?

00:47.840 --> 00:49.320
What are you saying?

00:49.400 --> 00:50.400
Amazing.

00:50.920 --> 00:55.600
My friends, under Mintu sir's
rocky leadership, judge--

00:56.720 --> 00:58.280
- Rock-steady.
- Okay.

00:58.360 --> 01:01.560
Under Mintu sir's rock-steady leadership,

01:01.640 --> 01:04.080
Judge Ghosh has accepted
the demands of the Bar!

01:04.160 --> 01:06.480
[cheering]

01:09.000 --> 01:12.160
So from now on,
in Delhi's blistering heat,

01:13.000 --> 01:18.440
no lawyer in Patparganj
will be required to wear a coat in court.

01:19.920 --> 01:21.520
So now, my fellow lawyers,

01:22.520 --> 01:26.480
let's start stripping these coats off!

01:28.840 --> 01:30.520
[chanting] President Mintu gets our vote!

01:30.600 --> 01:32.240
Thanks to him, no coats in court!

01:32.320 --> 01:34.600
President Mintu gets our vote!
Thanks to him, no coats in court!

01:34.680 --> 01:37.400
President Mintu gets our vote!
Thanks to him, no coats in court!

01:37.480 --> 01:39.200
President Mintu gets our vote!

01:39.280 --> 01:40.480
IF YOU WANT A PRESIDENT
WHO IS SMART,

01:40.560 --> 01:41.720
THEN SUPPORT MINTU
WITH YOUR HEART

01:41.800 --> 01:44.800
But, Tyagi sir, I really need
your approval on this. Please.

01:44.880 --> 01:48.360
- Was the issue with the wall sorted?
- Sir. [chuckles] Check this out, sir.

01:48.840 --> 01:50.440
Uh, here.

01:54.200 --> 01:55.400
KEEP THE COURT NEAT AND CLEAN

01:55.480 --> 01:57.120
- [Tyagi] Great.
- [Vishwas] Thank you, sir.

01:57.200 --> 02:01.400
- And the leakage in the courtroom?
- Yes, sir! Uh… here you go.

02:05.760 --> 02:07.840
- [Tyagi] Wow.
- [Vishwas] Everything's done, sir.

02:09.080 --> 02:11.360
Now just take a look at this
and give us your approval.

02:12.600 --> 02:14.960
The hallmark
of infrastructural development.

02:16.000 --> 02:17.680
[door creaks]

02:17.760 --> 02:19.480
- [Tyagi] Wow.
- [Vishwas] Thank you, sir.

02:19.560 --> 02:22.160
Uh, this toilet is all yours.

02:22.240 --> 02:24.520
[Shubhkela]
This isn't the… women's toilet, is it?

02:24.600 --> 02:26.480
- Huh? Spick and span.
- [chuckles]

02:26.560 --> 02:28.360
Isn't it, sir?
That's exactly what I thought.

02:29.120 --> 02:32.320
Tyagi sir, you won't lose
a single point on infrastructure!

02:32.400 --> 02:34.560
I worked really hard
for this portfolio visit.

02:34.640 --> 02:37.000
Don't worry,
I won't ask you to do it again.

02:37.080 --> 02:39.520
This is my first inspection
since I took over as judge.

02:39.600 --> 02:42.320
The High Court should feel
that even with Judge Bainsla gone,

02:42.400 --> 02:46.160
the Patparganj Court…
is still… in capable hands.

02:46.240 --> 02:47.880
- Of course it is! It is!
- Vishwas.

02:47.960 --> 02:50.640
You have four hours left
before the portfolio judge arrives.

02:50.720 --> 02:51.960
If there's anything left to do--

02:52.040 --> 02:54.160
Come on, Topo,
what are you worrying about?

02:54.800 --> 02:58.080
Sir, I challenge anyone to find
any issues with our infrastructure.

02:58.160 --> 02:59.840
I'll eat my words. [chuckles]

03:00.920 --> 03:02.200
- Really?
- Yes, sir.

03:02.280 --> 03:06.040
[screaming]

03:06.120 --> 03:08.320
What happened? What's going on?

03:09.680 --> 03:11.560
[Topo] Hey, step aside. Move, move!

03:11.640 --> 03:13.680
- Move, move! Step aside.
- He got a terrible electrical shock!

03:13.760 --> 03:14.960
[advocate] He's still vibrating.

03:17.360 --> 03:19.400
- Hey.
- [whimpering]

03:23.000 --> 03:24.920
- What did you touch?
- [bystander] The gate.

03:27.200 --> 03:31.280
Sir, the electric cable, the iron gate
and his hand all got stuck together.

03:34.440 --> 03:35.760
Vishwas.

03:37.360 --> 03:38.760
[clears throat] Yes, sir?

03:38.840 --> 03:43.040
Didn't you just say that if anyone finds
any issues with our infrastructure,

03:43.120 --> 03:44.520
you'll eat your words?

03:44.600 --> 03:46.400
- Yes, sir.
- Then what's this?

03:47.040 --> 03:48.360
An issue, sir.

03:48.440 --> 03:50.280
- [Ghosh] Murli! Murli?
- [whimpering continues]

03:51.880 --> 03:52.880
Are you okay?

03:52.960 --> 03:55.200
That happens to be Judge Ghosh's reader.

03:58.160 --> 03:59.720
A major issue, sir.

04:00.320 --> 04:02.360
- Vishwas.
- [Ghosh] Are you okay?

04:06.400 --> 04:08.160
How did he get electrocuted?

04:11.360 --> 04:12.560
[theme music plays]

04:24.200 --> 04:25.280
[theme music stops]

04:25.360 --> 04:26.400
- [slaps]
- [client 1 screams]

04:26.480 --> 04:27.480
[client 2] You bitch!

04:27.560 --> 04:29.760
Came to borrow the sugar,
and you borrowed my husband!

04:29.840 --> 04:30.880
I'm gonna kill you.

04:30.960 --> 04:33.480
- Don't you have any shame?
- [all clamouring]

04:33.560 --> 04:36.560
Mediation. The court's last attempt
to prevent a family break up.

04:36.640 --> 04:38.560
- [client 1 screams]
- But we want a break up.

04:38.640 --> 04:40.880
Then you'll have to take
a beating from your daughter-in-law.

04:40.960 --> 04:43.080
- What? [gasps]
- Like a dog.

04:43.160 --> 04:44.600
You will provoke her,

04:44.680 --> 04:46.640
and she'll beat you up
in front of the mediator.

04:46.720 --> 04:47.720
Really?

04:47.800 --> 04:50.160
He will immediately transfer
your case to the court.

04:50.800 --> 04:52.520
[chuckles] Oh, I see!

04:52.600 --> 04:54.440
And there, we'll show the video
of you being beaten up.

04:54.520 --> 04:55.520
Okay.

04:55.600 --> 04:57.960
- Look, he's filming. [chuckles]
- Right.

04:59.160 --> 05:01.240
[family member] Stop this fight.
It's getting out of control.

05:02.520 --> 05:04.120
Ma'am, isn't there any other way?

05:05.160 --> 05:09.280
My dear sir, you've asked for a divorce
on the grounds of mental cruelty.

05:09.360 --> 05:11.200
Do you know how hard it is
to prove that in court?

05:11.280 --> 05:13.760
But we're telling you
that we're being treated with cruelty.

05:13.840 --> 05:14.840
So what's the problem?

05:14.920 --> 05:17.960
But, madam, the law doesn't
clearly define what is mental cruelty.

05:18.040 --> 05:21.360
I mean, someone may say
that his wife talks dirty to him

05:21.440 --> 05:22.840
- and that's cruelty.
- [mother] It is.

05:22.920 --> 05:25.440
And someone else may say
that his wife never talks dirty to him

05:26.200 --> 05:27.200
and that's cruelty.

05:27.280 --> 05:30.200
What should the law go by?
Dirty language or dirty talk?

05:30.280 --> 05:31.320
That is true.

05:31.400 --> 05:33.560
What's cruelty to one
is love to someone else.

05:33.640 --> 05:37.080
- [mother] I see.
- That's why divorce cases go on for years.

05:37.160 --> 05:38.160
Hmm.

05:38.240 --> 05:39.640
[clamouring continues]

05:39.720 --> 05:43.720
- Mom…
- Nannu, don't you worry about me.

05:43.800 --> 05:45.120
You just watch.

05:45.200 --> 05:48.280
Your mama's going to get beaten up
like a dog for you in there.

05:48.360 --> 05:51.160
I'm going to make sure
you get divorced today!

05:51.240 --> 05:52.960
Madam, you should go in
with your hair open.

05:53.040 --> 05:54.440
What? Why should I do that?

05:54.520 --> 05:56.440
- Because the better the grip…
- [mother] Yeah?

05:56.520 --> 05:58.120
…the harder she can slap you around.

05:58.200 --> 06:01.000
Oh, wow! That's a very good idea.

06:01.080 --> 06:02.560
- Yes, I'll wear my hair loose.
- Of course.

06:02.640 --> 06:03.640
- No problem at all.
- Excellent.

06:03.720 --> 06:05.040
- I'm ready to be beaten up.
- Absolutely.

06:05.120 --> 06:06.800
- Let's go in and do this.
- Come on, madam.

06:06.880 --> 06:08.400
- Let's go in. Very good.
- Come, Nannu.

06:08.480 --> 06:10.000
- [Daleel] Come on, madam.
- [phone chimes]

06:12.440 --> 06:14.200
[Mintu] Fifty shades of Mintu.

06:14.280 --> 06:18.040
May I see one of yours, please?

06:18.120 --> 06:20.440
No, Vishwas, no way.

06:20.520 --> 06:22.080
If you'd just told me
you were going to surprise me,

06:22.160 --> 06:23.560
I would've stopped you from coming.

06:23.640 --> 06:25.440
We had a huge problem
in court today, so I--

06:25.520 --> 06:27.000
So why leave me here with Ani?

06:27.800 --> 06:31.400
You know quite well that she knows
I have a bit of a problem with her.

06:31.480 --> 06:34.600
But she also knows that you know that
there'll never be anything between us.

06:34.680 --> 06:37.680
Vishwas, I'm perfectly okay
sitting here on my own.

06:37.760 --> 06:39.480
But I already called her here.

06:39.560 --> 06:40.560
She'll feel really bad.

06:41.440 --> 06:44.120
Look, Ani's the sensitive type, you know?

06:45.880 --> 06:48.280
No, I mean… it'll hurt her feelings.

06:48.360 --> 06:50.800
- Yeah.
- [Ani] Guys?

06:51.440 --> 06:52.680
I-I can hear you.

06:52.760 --> 06:54.080
Okay.

06:54.160 --> 06:55.440
Come on now, please.

06:55.520 --> 06:57.360
But… what will we talk about?

06:57.440 --> 06:58.800
You can bitch about me.

06:58.880 --> 07:00.280
Ani? Come on. Come on.

07:01.240 --> 07:02.600
- You know Varsha, right?
- Of course.

07:02.680 --> 07:03.680
Varsha, you know Ani.

07:03.760 --> 07:04.760
- Hi.
- That's great.

07:06.520 --> 07:09.480
Now you two besties sit down and chat.
I'll be back in a bit, yeah?

07:09.560 --> 07:10.560
[chuckles]

07:11.960 --> 07:13.480
[client] You wait and see
what I do to you!

07:13.560 --> 07:15.080
[client 2] This isn't a family court.

07:15.160 --> 07:16.520
It's a boxing ring!

07:16.600 --> 07:18.240
[client 3] Easy, guys, easy!

07:18.320 --> 07:20.320
- She broke my head, bloody imbecile.
- Who are these people?

07:20.400 --> 07:22.840
Oh, my God.
They almost split his head open!

07:23.440 --> 07:25.120
- [Shukla] These people are the limit.
- Mr Singh?

07:26.160 --> 07:27.440
Uh, sir?

07:37.440 --> 07:42.400
Look, you two are
our third couple for the day.

07:43.160 --> 07:45.960
Matters, this time, will not
escalate to physical violence.

07:47.640 --> 07:51.640
Everyone will conduct themselves
in a civilised manner.

07:52.760 --> 07:56.000
So tell me, what kind
of cruelty have you faced?

07:56.080 --> 07:58.400
- Sir, I--
- [mother] Where do I even begin, sir?

07:59.480 --> 08:02.600
She roams around the house
all day in her underwear.

08:02.680 --> 08:06.040
When I tell her, "Change your clothes,"
she says "Change your thinking."

08:06.120 --> 08:07.480
She came to us with nothing,

08:07.560 --> 08:09.600
but she has the money
to shop online all day.

08:09.680 --> 08:11.680
This sleeping beauty
wakes up at 10:00 every morning.

08:11.760 --> 08:14.040
By the time Nihal comes home,
it's 11:00 at night.

08:14.120 --> 08:15.280
He hardly walks through the door

08:15.360 --> 08:17.400
when she grabs him
and forces him spend time with her.

08:17.480 --> 08:19.880
[mother] Right, and why should
he come to you first? Tell me.

08:19.960 --> 08:21.760
To indulge your debauchery? [scoffs]

08:21.840 --> 08:24.680
Sir, is it debauchery
to be intimate with one's husband?

08:24.760 --> 08:27.320
- Yes, it is! It is debauchery!
- Really? I see.

08:27.400 --> 08:30.160
When she clearly doesn't want
to have a child… then it's debauchery!

08:31.000 --> 08:32.680
Instead of listening to nursery rhymes,

08:32.760 --> 08:35.240
this wretched girl
listens to steamy love songs.

08:35.320 --> 08:36.920
"Touch me baby. I want to feel your body."

08:37.000 --> 08:38.760
Honestly, shame on her!

08:38.840 --> 08:41.720
Sujata madam, I don't know how
this ugly, angry bird managed

08:41.800 --> 08:42.880
to get into our family.

08:42.960 --> 08:44.120
- She has no shame at all.
- It's okay.

08:44.200 --> 08:46.320
Are these the values
her parents brought her up with?

08:46.400 --> 08:48.480
Hey! Don't you dare insult my parents!

08:48.560 --> 08:49.720
- Mind your manners!
- Really, huh?

08:49.800 --> 08:51.760
- Mind my manners?
- She's talking shit about our parents.

08:51.840 --> 08:54.520
You just sit tight in your chair
otherwise you'll take off into the air.

08:54.600 --> 08:57.000
At the slightest thing this midget
takes off like a mini helicopter.

08:57.080 --> 08:58.280
Listen, madam.

08:58.360 --> 09:00.800
All of you please calm down
one minute, okay?

09:00.880 --> 09:03.760
My dear, before you got married,

09:03.840 --> 09:06.560
did you inform them
that you didn't want children?

09:06.640 --> 09:08.240
- No.
- Sir, I want to have children.

09:08.320 --> 09:10.200
I just don't want to have children
in their house!

09:10.280 --> 09:12.880
You have no idea
what a crazy control freak she is.

09:12.960 --> 09:14.480
Nihal doesn't dare
to speak in front of her.

09:14.560 --> 09:15.560
What?

09:15.640 --> 09:18.080
Hey, this is called good upbringing.

09:18.800 --> 09:21.080
But how can I expect
a bimbette like her to understand?

09:21.160 --> 09:22.760
Sir, during our wedding celebration,

09:22.840 --> 09:24.320
do you know what song she made Nihal sing?

09:24.960 --> 09:27.800
Some song about how much
a son loves his mother.

09:27.880 --> 09:29.280
[mother] Yes, so what about it?

09:29.360 --> 09:30.680
- What's wrong with it?
- Very beautiful.

09:30.760 --> 09:32.440
It's such a beautiful
and sacred relationship.

09:32.520 --> 09:33.760
Don't you love your mother, Nannu?

09:33.840 --> 09:35.680
Is it a Mother's day celebration?
It was my wedding.

09:35.760 --> 09:37.240
A son can't sing
to his mother at his wedding?

09:37.320 --> 09:39.960
Sir, I don't want to stay there anymore.
I just want to move out!

09:40.040 --> 09:41.720
And if Nihal is ready and willing,

09:41.800 --> 09:44.240
I'm happy to withdraw
the divorce petition today, Nihal!

09:44.320 --> 09:47.080
- No, no, no, my Nihal isn't ready.
- She will decide.

09:47.160 --> 09:48.440
[mother] Why should you move out?

09:48.520 --> 09:50.560
Sir, it's a mother-in-law's right
to live with her family.

09:50.640 --> 09:51.880
The Jharkhand High Court has said so.

09:51.960 --> 09:54.240
But what about
the daughter-in-law's rights, madam?

09:54.320 --> 09:56.480
My dear, a daughter-in-law
can only have rights

09:56.560 --> 09:58.360
after she becomes a mother-in-law.

09:58.440 --> 10:01.080
Because rights like these
are always enforced.

10:01.160 --> 10:04.520
- Enforced by the son, not by the husband.
- Yeah, he's right.

10:05.120 --> 10:07.200
So how long
should I keep tolerating her taunts?

10:07.280 --> 10:09.440
Why don't you guys get together
and decide for me?

10:09.520 --> 10:12.480
My dear, taunts are
a form of love language here.

10:12.560 --> 10:13.880
Yes, sir, very true.

10:15.400 --> 10:17.840
Tell me something. What are you?

10:19.480 --> 10:20.880
- What does he mean?
- What am I?

10:20.960 --> 10:24.480
You are a daughter-in-law, right?

10:25.280 --> 10:27.920
- And, madam, what are you?
- What am I?

10:28.000 --> 10:30.360
A mother-in-law, right?

10:30.440 --> 10:35.840
Now, only when in-laws are in sync
can there be a happy family!

10:36.960 --> 10:39.320
- Wow, sir, that's excellent!
- Amazing, sir!

10:39.400 --> 10:41.360
- Brilliant, sir. Brilliant!
- Amazing, sir. Bravo!

10:41.440 --> 10:43.480
But, sir, we don't want
to have a family with her.

10:44.080 --> 10:46.400
Do you see any signs
of her wanting to settle down?

10:46.480 --> 10:48.920
We just want to be rid of this wretch
and her wretched family!

10:49.000 --> 10:50.920
Hey, haven't I told you already
not to insult my family?

10:51.000 --> 10:52.320
I'll shoot you right where you're sitting!

10:52.400 --> 10:53.560
You think that's going to scare us?

10:53.640 --> 10:55.280
She's talking such bullshit!
She thinks I can't shoot!

10:55.360 --> 10:56.840
Hey, Captain Blackbeard, calm down.

10:56.920 --> 10:58.080
No, no, come on. Come on!

10:58.160 --> 10:59.760
Shoot me. I'm ready for it. Go for it.

10:59.840 --> 11:01.720
Ma'am, you're a lady. What are you doing?

11:01.800 --> 11:03.440
What does this midget think of himself?

11:03.520 --> 11:04.880
Who does he think I am?

11:04.960 --> 11:06.600
I may be a lady, but I'm not an idiot!

11:06.680 --> 11:08.240
See, I'm ready. Let's see you do it!

11:08.320 --> 11:09.840
- Everyone, quiet!
- Stop yelling, everyone.

11:09.920 --> 11:12.840
- I'm not feeling well, please!
- Me too. [breathes heavily]

11:12.920 --> 11:13.920
I'm not feeling good.

11:14.000 --> 11:15.480
Blood pressure's rising.

11:15.560 --> 11:18.400
I'll tell you what,
let's meet in one hour.

11:18.480 --> 11:21.040
We'll take a chill pill
and some of this as well.

11:28.680 --> 11:30.280
[burps]

11:30.360 --> 11:33.680
- This happens today of all days.
- [chuckles]

11:35.680 --> 11:39.840
No, I mean,
it would've been bad on any day.

11:39.920 --> 11:41.040
But today?

11:43.360 --> 11:46.120
What's more… it's Mr Ghosh's reader.

11:47.240 --> 11:48.240
[chuckles]

11:48.320 --> 11:50.480
If it happened to any other reader,
it would have still been bad.

11:50.560 --> 11:52.280
But Ghosh's?

11:52.360 --> 11:54.800
You guys know
what kind of man Mr Ghosh is.

11:54.880 --> 11:56.120
He's going to chew my brains.

11:56.840 --> 12:01.120
Your Honour, I'm aware
that I made a big mistake.

12:02.040 --> 12:06.040
It's the day of the portfolio visit.
I should never have touched the gate.

12:06.680 --> 12:11.720
Murli, you're making yet another mistake.
What's that?

12:17.080 --> 12:19.640
Sir, I didn't want
to make a complaint at all.

12:20.400 --> 12:23.240
But Mr Ghosh said,
"What about the reasonable observer?"

12:24.000 --> 12:26.960
Now, how could I refuse
to follow Mr Ghosh's order, sir?

12:27.040 --> 12:30.600
I knew Mr Ghosh's "judge-itis"
would kick in soon.

12:30.680 --> 12:32.920
He just needed a chance
to show how much he knows.

12:33.000 --> 12:34.400
He can't wait to show everyone

12:34.480 --> 12:36.680
that he's the one and only,
truly great judge,

12:36.760 --> 12:39.400
while the rest of us
are here just to pass time!

12:39.480 --> 12:42.200
Sir, this reasonable observer
is who exactly?

12:42.800 --> 12:44.160
[Shubhkela] The common man.

12:44.240 --> 12:46.600
According to the principles
of judicial conduct,

12:46.680 --> 12:49.520
there should never be
any doubts about judicial integrity

12:49.600 --> 12:51.280
in the eyes of the common man.

12:51.880 --> 12:55.280
Which means, even though
we lose a few points on infrastructure,

12:56.760 --> 12:58.520
the PDJ has to take action.

13:01.200 --> 13:04.440
Sir, action or strict action?

13:04.520 --> 13:05.720
What's the difference?

13:05.800 --> 13:08.200
To take an action,
we first set up an inquiry.

13:08.280 --> 13:11.240
We do a weekend to weekend investigation
and find the root cause.

13:11.320 --> 13:13.160
To determine
the strength of the root cause,

13:13.240 --> 13:14.600
we set up another enquiry.

13:14.680 --> 13:16.640
Then we do
a weekend to weekend investigation.

13:16.720 --> 13:18.480
- And so on and so forth.
- And strict action?

13:18.560 --> 13:20.120
The same, sir, but strictly.

13:22.400 --> 13:24.000
[chuckles] He'll go a long way.

13:24.080 --> 13:25.440
Thank you, sir.

13:25.520 --> 13:27.080
- Vishwas?
- Sir?

13:27.160 --> 13:29.960
You have only two hours to do this.

13:30.040 --> 13:31.320
That strictly, sir?

13:31.400 --> 13:32.480
Vishwas, listen to me.

13:32.560 --> 13:34.400
Before this portfolio visit takes place,

13:34.480 --> 13:38.920
I want this matter,
this chapter to be closed forever. Finito!

13:39.000 --> 13:42.560
- Yes, sir!
- And-- Look at him. Look at his eyes!

13:42.640 --> 13:44.920
Get two bowls
so he can drop his eyes into them.

13:45.000 --> 13:46.960
And give him some water.

13:47.040 --> 13:48.680
Why did you have to fiddle
with that stupid gate?

13:48.760 --> 13:50.160
You could've fiddled with something else.

13:50.240 --> 13:52.080
[chuckles]

13:52.160 --> 13:53.840
S-Sonam's pregnant?

13:53.920 --> 13:56.280
Yes. Her lawyer's the one who told me.

13:56.360 --> 13:57.360
\SUJATA NEGI

13:57.440 --> 13:59.640
\- And, you know, lawyers never lie.
- Until after they switch sides.

13:59.720 --> 14:03.000
Now, you haven't been
living together for six months, right?

14:03.080 --> 14:05.000
And the girl isn't even showing yet.

14:05.080 --> 14:07.800
So that means
something happened two months ago.

14:08.400 --> 14:10.400
And here she's acting
like she doesn't want a child.

14:10.480 --> 14:11.480
[Daleel] Mm-hmm.

14:11.560 --> 14:12.680
\Madam has a boyfriend.

14:12.760 --> 14:13.880
[scoffs]

14:13.960 --> 14:15.760
So your Sonam is also unfaithful.

14:15.840 --> 14:20.880
Well… we met up two months ago.

14:22.880 --> 14:24.880
It was our anniversary.

14:24.960 --> 14:28.600
So we got a little naughty,
and we partied without hats.

14:28.680 --> 14:29.680
[chuckles]

14:31.200 --> 14:33.640
You… you know what I mean?

14:34.280 --> 14:36.360
So the father-to-be is you?

14:37.280 --> 14:40.240
That means a divorce
will be almost impossible to get.

14:40.320 --> 14:42.440
- I don't want a divorce.
- [exclaims]

14:43.800 --> 14:46.880
I love Sonam with all my heart.
I want to stay with her.

14:46.960 --> 14:48.240
Why didn't you say so before?

14:48.320 --> 14:51.200
When could I have done that?
Mama just went to the washroom.

14:51.280 --> 14:53.600
Hey, at sometime, you'll have to open
your mouth in front of your mother.

14:54.720 --> 14:59.120
[stammers] With a name like Nannu,
how can I open my mouth in front of her?

14:59.200 --> 15:02.440
Ma'am, Sonam's brother is hot-tempered.

15:03.200 --> 15:05.840
If his mother provokes him
even a little bit,

15:05.920 --> 15:07.920
there'll be a fight
in front of the mediator for sure.

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
Downloaded from -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

15:09.600 --> 15:12.680
Ma'am, can you think of a way
where only Sonam and I could meet?

15:12.760 --> 15:14.080
Alone?

15:14.160 --> 15:15.720
I'll make everything right. I swear.

15:23.080 --> 15:25.200
Okay, I'll arrange it.

15:27.320 --> 15:29.520
Sir, you complained
when there was no electricity.

15:29.600 --> 15:31.320
Now you're complaining when you have it.

15:31.400 --> 15:33.520
We're not complaining
about the electric supply,

15:33.600 --> 15:35.400
we're complaining
about the electric shock.

15:35.480 --> 15:38.320
Sir, I'm from Transmission,
in charge of supply.

15:38.400 --> 15:41.320
The shock was caused
by the hanging wire touching the gate.

15:41.400 --> 15:43.480
The Maintenance department is to blame.

15:44.320 --> 15:46.120
According to the maintenance schedule,

15:46.200 --> 15:48.760
this pole will be checked
only after four months.

15:48.840 --> 15:50.040
So?

15:50.120 --> 15:53.240
So after four months,
if there's still a problem, I'll fix it.

15:54.040 --> 15:56.320
It's not like problems show up
according to your schedule.

15:56.400 --> 15:57.760
We have a problem now.

16:00.000 --> 16:04.880
It's been wrongly installed, sir.
This is their fault. Yeah.

16:05.560 --> 16:08.040
Sir, from what I see,
the pole's been installed perfectly.

16:08.840 --> 16:11.440
Would you like me to show you?
Should I touch it?

16:11.520 --> 16:13.280
- No.
- Show me.

16:13.360 --> 16:14.360
Yeah, show us.

16:14.440 --> 16:15.440
Show me.

16:17.400 --> 16:20.560
But when the electricity department
isn't to blame, why should I touch it?

16:20.640 --> 16:21.640
Shut up.

16:22.440 --> 16:25.880
It was an electric shock.
And your department's not to blame?

16:26.760 --> 16:28.720
- What about the water?
- What water?

16:28.800 --> 16:29.800
There.

16:29.880 --> 16:32.880
Sir, he got a shock
because there's water in that pothole.

16:32.960 --> 16:34.800
The Municipal Corporation is at fault.

16:34.880 --> 16:36.040
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

16:37.240 --> 16:40.840
If the pothole had been on the road,
it would've been our fault.

16:42.320 --> 16:45.680
But its under the gate of the court,
so the court is to blame.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.600
Sir, the court is asking you
who's to blame,

16:48.680 --> 16:50.560
and you're blaming
it back on the court, huh?

16:51.240 --> 16:53.760
How else do you think
he became a senior officer?

16:56.240 --> 16:58.520
The late Patpardas Pandey.

16:58.600 --> 17:01.480
Sir, the gate that was responsible
for Murli's electric shock,

17:01.560 --> 17:03.240
it doesn't have any earthing at all, sir.

17:04.000 --> 17:05.520
And the gate was installed way back

17:05.600 --> 17:07.720
- in 19… 72. Yeah.
- '72.

17:08.560 --> 17:10.720
- By the late Mr Patpardas Pandey.
- Yeah.

17:10.800 --> 17:14.520
And since he can't appear in court
to blame anyone else,

17:15.760 --> 17:19.240
we can quite confidently say
he's to blame for this incident.

17:20.280 --> 17:23.640
So will Mr Ghosh's
reasonable observer accept this?

17:23.720 --> 17:25.680
- Uh-huh.
- [Tyagi] No way.

17:25.760 --> 17:29.640
We need to find something solid,
so he doesn't pick holes in it.

17:29.720 --> 17:30.960
Something better.

17:31.680 --> 17:32.960
Rock solid.

17:33.040 --> 17:37.560
Sir, is it possible to find someone
better than a dead person?

17:49.280 --> 17:50.560
Yes, it is, Vishwas.

17:50.640 --> 17:53.960
- Act of God.
- Act of God?

17:54.040 --> 17:57.360
Sir, the pothole was full of water
because it had rained one week ago.

17:58.160 --> 18:00.480
Act of God.
The wire was hanging from the pole

18:00.560 --> 18:02.800
because there was
a storm along with the rain.

18:03.280 --> 18:04.280
Act of God.

18:04.360 --> 18:09.600
If Murli had been wearing normal shoes,
the shock would've had less of an impact.

18:09.680 --> 18:12.080
But he's been using steel crutches
to walk since childhood.

18:12.720 --> 18:14.520
Polio. Act of God.

18:15.640 --> 18:16.640
Poor Murli.

18:18.440 --> 18:19.440
[Ghosh] Excuse me.

18:20.280 --> 18:24.960
The Act of God clause is only applicable
when the event is unforeseeable.

18:25.720 --> 18:26.720
[Vishwas] Yes, sir.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.200
On the 18th to be precise,

18:30.040 --> 18:33.400
I'd complained about the potholes
in the court premises.

18:33.480 --> 18:34.760
See for yourself.

18:35.800 --> 18:39.000
Mr Tyagi, it's not an act of God.

18:39.920 --> 18:41.160
It's an act of negligence.

18:41.800 --> 18:43.280
So, if you don't mind,

18:43.360 --> 18:47.200
may I bring up this negligence
in front of the portfolio judge?

18:48.520 --> 18:53.720
And I hope, you will only want that
that is good for the court,

18:54.720 --> 18:57.120
not what's good for your report.

18:58.200 --> 18:59.480
You're one of a kind.

19:01.200 --> 19:03.840
The once in a lifetime,
once in a millennium kind.

19:03.920 --> 19:05.960
[both laughing]

19:06.640 --> 19:09.520
But, honestly,
what made you think we wouldn't bond?

19:10.760 --> 19:14.240
Genuinely, Varsha, there's nothing at all
between Vishwas and me.

19:14.320 --> 19:15.480
We're just friends.

19:16.160 --> 19:18.640
But anyone would be
a little jealous of you, Ani.

19:18.720 --> 19:20.840
Anyway, I'm here for a specific reason.

19:20.920 --> 19:21.920
What?

19:24.680 --> 19:25.680
[gasps]

19:25.760 --> 19:29.720
- To propose.
- Oh, my God, that is so beautiful!

19:29.800 --> 19:31.320
How are you planning to do it?

19:31.400 --> 19:33.560
There's only one thing
that Vishwas appreciates.

19:34.400 --> 19:35.840
Tea and junk food.

19:37.080 --> 19:40.360
So, I'll put the ring
on his finger while eating.

19:41.040 --> 19:42.200
Right here.

19:43.720 --> 19:45.240
[chuckles] In the office?

19:46.120 --> 19:47.120
You know what?

19:47.880 --> 19:50.760
Let's order those snacks
from Mangesh, Vishwas' favourite!

19:50.840 --> 19:53.800
Wait, I brought some from Anand Snacks.

19:53.880 --> 19:54.960
Vishwas' favourite.

19:55.040 --> 19:56.920
Are you sure?
I think he only orders from Anand

19:57.000 --> 19:59.480
when Mangesh is closed or something.

19:59.560 --> 20:01.360
I am very sure, Ani.

20:02.520 --> 20:04.600
I know that much about my fiancé, right?

20:07.320 --> 20:08.480
[chuckles] Of course.

20:08.560 --> 20:13.200
Sir, now I'd like to tell you
just how disgusting this family is!

20:13.280 --> 20:15.320
I mean, their parents are just the pits.

20:15.400 --> 20:17.560
They haven't taught
their children any manners.

20:17.640 --> 20:20.080
All they do is fight with everyone.

20:20.160 --> 20:23.560
They're such vulgar people.
So crude and cheap!

20:33.000 --> 20:34.960
Why didn't you tell me you were pregnant?

20:35.800 --> 20:37.640
I'm thinking of aborting it.

20:37.720 --> 20:39.720
[sombre music plays]

20:40.520 --> 20:41.520
Come on, Sonam.

20:41.600 --> 20:44.800
We'll be fighting over custody
and visitation rights.

20:46.120 --> 20:47.800
Is that how you wanna bring up a child?

20:47.880 --> 20:50.560
Sonam, let's try one more time, please.

20:50.640 --> 20:54.320
If you come back to me,
I'll take care of everything.

20:54.400 --> 20:55.520
What?

20:56.240 --> 20:57.280
What will you do?

20:58.520 --> 20:59.880
What will change this time?

21:01.080 --> 21:02.680
I'll go back with Nihal,

21:03.480 --> 21:05.480
but Nannu is the one
I'll have to live with right?

21:06.040 --> 21:08.120
Have you ever wondered, Sonam,

21:08.200 --> 21:10.720
why a marriage can take place
without the court's permission

21:10.800 --> 21:12.320
but not a divorce?

21:13.080 --> 21:14.840
Because even a court knows

21:14.920 --> 21:17.520
that society cannot be built
with broken homes.

21:18.800 --> 21:21.520
That's why it gives you
so many chances to reconcile.

21:23.680 --> 21:25.640
You got married of your own free will.

21:26.160 --> 21:27.520
You love each other.

21:28.160 --> 21:29.920
You're about to start a family.

21:30.000 --> 21:32.240
[sighs]

21:33.160 --> 21:35.000
[Sujata]
Not everyone gets this opportunity.

21:36.760 --> 21:38.920
Living alone can be very cruel.

21:39.560 --> 21:40.760
There's nothing worse.

21:45.720 --> 21:47.720
Sonam, I'm aware that Mama is wrong…

21:50.560 --> 21:52.240
but she is my mother.

21:55.440 --> 22:00.600
Now that Papa's gone, it's… only me.

22:02.360 --> 22:04.320
I can't just abandon her, can I?

22:04.400 --> 22:06.240
But Nihal,
it's only after I've tried and lost

22:06.320 --> 22:07.960
that I'm saying we should move out.

22:08.040 --> 22:12.520
You go off to work, and all day long
your mama's taunts I have to endure.

22:12.600 --> 22:14.880
And whenever I talk to you about it,
what do you say?

22:14.960 --> 22:18.120
"Ignore it, it will all be fine.
Ignore it, it will all be fine."

22:18.200 --> 22:19.520
How much more?

22:24.040 --> 22:25.240
It's my fault.

22:27.840 --> 22:29.640
I should've made Mama understand.

22:33.960 --> 22:36.320
And I should have
sung for you at the wedding.

22:39.480 --> 22:40.640
[Sujata] Well, you can sing now.

22:40.720 --> 22:42.800
What's the problem? I'll play the beat--

22:42.880 --> 22:44.720
Hey, wait! No.

22:46.160 --> 22:49.840
Nihal, you will have to sing
in front of your mama for me.

22:49.920 --> 22:51.760
[stammers] In front of my mama?

22:52.640 --> 22:53.680
Will you?

22:54.960 --> 22:55.960
This way, sir.

22:56.520 --> 22:58.640
Sir, you'll find dustbins
all over the premises.

22:58.720 --> 22:59.760
Cleanliness is important.

22:59.840 --> 23:01.720
And this is our one-window clearance.

23:01.800 --> 23:04.800
Whatever your problem,
come to this window, and it'll be solved.

23:05.960 --> 23:08.880
Sir, we've made sure
Patparganj Court is disabled-friendly,

23:08.960 --> 23:10.720
that's why we built this ramp.

23:13.000 --> 23:17.160
What does this say?
"It takes time, patience is imperative."

23:17.240 --> 23:19.480
The path to justice
is still at a distance.

23:20.080 --> 23:21.800
Wow. Wonderful thought.

23:22.560 --> 23:23.720
- Note it down.
- Yes, sir.

23:23.800 --> 23:25.880
Sir, I come to work every morning
with this in mind.

23:25.960 --> 23:26.960
This way.

23:28.920 --> 23:29.920
[grunts]

23:31.400 --> 23:32.840
[gasps]

23:32.920 --> 23:34.040
[chuckles]

23:34.600 --> 23:37.560
Sir, this is Shambhu.
You know about the monkey problem, right?

23:37.640 --> 23:38.840
- [chuckles]
- Yes.

23:38.920 --> 23:40.400
Come, sir. Please, come.

23:44.840 --> 23:46.160
[breathing heavily]

23:51.960 --> 23:54.320
- Uh…
- Uh, he…

23:54.400 --> 23:55.920
Do come, sir, a lot to see.

23:57.640 --> 23:59.720
- [judge] Oh, fire extinguisher!
- [Tyagi] Yes, sir.

23:59.800 --> 24:00.800
[chuckles]

24:03.560 --> 24:05.280
Sir, there used to be two fans earlier.

24:05.360 --> 24:07.920
Now we've had
two new air conditioners installed there.

24:08.000 --> 24:09.880
We're trying to make it more hi-tech, sir.

24:09.960 --> 24:11.400
Come, let's take a look at the washroom.

24:11.480 --> 24:13.280
- Let's go.
- Come. Please.

24:13.360 --> 24:14.960
[judge urinating]

24:17.640 --> 24:19.360
[Vishwas] He didn't pull the flush.

24:24.400 --> 24:26.760
Mr Tyagi, I was a little sceptical

24:27.880 --> 24:30.680
because Justice Bainsla
is a tough act to follow.

24:31.400 --> 24:34.480
But you have put me at ease.

24:35.320 --> 24:37.920
You are picking up
from where she left off.

24:38.000 --> 24:41.200
There are a lot
of infrastructural improvements already.

24:41.280 --> 24:42.720
- Thank you, sir.
- All right.

24:42.800 --> 24:44.360
For formality's sake,

24:45.160 --> 24:46.760
let's get some peer feedback.

24:48.240 --> 24:51.200
I'm sure, uh,
they'll have good things to say.

24:52.240 --> 24:53.520
Who is that judge?

24:54.000 --> 24:58.000
Oh! Justice Ghosh. I'll meet him.

25:03.640 --> 25:05.160
[stammers]

25:05.240 --> 25:06.840
[sings]

25:13.480 --> 25:14.560
That's it.

25:15.920 --> 25:16.960
Yes, go on.

25:20.600 --> 25:22.120
Son, try singing it.

25:23.280 --> 25:25.440
Can't you see, sir,
my son doesn't want to sing this song.

25:25.520 --> 25:27.080
Madam, you've been barking for two hours!

25:28.440 --> 25:30.800
I mean… you've been speaking.

25:31.600 --> 25:35.080
Now, why don't you give your son
a chance to say what he has to say.

25:35.840 --> 25:36.840
Go on, son.

25:36.920 --> 25:38.520
[singing continues]

25:42.040 --> 25:44.000
Just wait till we get home.

25:44.080 --> 25:46.160
I'll sort you out. Sit down!

25:48.600 --> 25:50.280
[laughs]

25:50.360 --> 25:52.120
You see that, sir?

25:52.200 --> 25:53.640
Don't you worry, Nannu.

25:53.720 --> 25:56.840
In less than a month, I'll find
a brand new daughter-in-law for us.

25:56.920 --> 25:58.880
I'll show her what I'm capable of.

25:58.960 --> 26:00.200
[laughs]

26:00.280 --> 26:02.200
- Come back after week and a half.
- What did you say?

26:02.280 --> 26:03.760
- After a week and a half!
- [Sonam] No, sir.

26:04.400 --> 26:07.000
I don't wanna come back.
Let's finish this. I've had enough.

26:07.080 --> 26:08.600
[mother] Why wait one and a half weeks?

26:08.680 --> 26:11.160
What will we achieve?
She's already spoken her mind, right?

26:11.240 --> 26:12.880
Do you think there's any hope, huh?

26:12.960 --> 26:14.960
We won't come back.
Just wrap this up now, please!

26:15.040 --> 26:17.680
We don't want anything from them. [scoffs]
What can they give us anyway?

26:17.760 --> 26:19.160
[laughs]

26:19.240 --> 26:22.640
What if their child takes after
this tiny, little midget uncle?

26:22.720 --> 26:25.320
Who wants a grandson who's 4'8"?

26:25.400 --> 26:27.360
[chuckles] I certainly don't.

26:27.440 --> 26:28.840
Finish it, finish it! [chuckles]

26:28.920 --> 26:30.560
Their whole family's full of midgets.

26:30.640 --> 26:32.160
Hey!

26:32.240 --> 26:34.520
See! I didn't even realise
the poor fellow is standing up!

26:34.600 --> 26:36.400
Didn't I tell you not to insult my family?

26:36.480 --> 26:38.040
So, what are you going to do?

26:38.120 --> 26:39.520
Let's see what you do.

26:39.600 --> 26:40.840
I've already said it twice now.

26:40.920 --> 26:43.120
You better stop insulting my family, okay?

26:43.200 --> 26:45.440
You think I can't bloody shoot?
Just watch me go for it!

27:24.680 --> 27:26.200
You come here, Nannu!

27:26.280 --> 27:27.720
What are you doing? Are you insane?

27:27.800 --> 27:29.600
[brother]
I'll shoot her bloody brains out!

27:52.840 --> 27:54.120
[judges laughing]

27:54.200 --> 27:55.200
[gunshot]

27:55.280 --> 27:57.840
Man, who's setting off firecrackers here?

27:57.920 --> 27:58.920
I'll just find out.

27:59.000 --> 28:01.560
- Justice Ghosh, sir.
- Hello, sir. How are you?

28:03.200 --> 28:04.200
That's it.

28:05.320 --> 28:06.800
He's got the report, nothing we can do.

28:06.880 --> 28:08.440
- [sobs]
- What?

28:09.400 --> 28:11.520
- I have a government job, sir.
- [Tyagi sucks teeth]

28:11.600 --> 28:14.640
Don't worry, Vishwas.
You must own some land back home?

28:14.720 --> 28:16.040
No, sir.

28:16.120 --> 28:17.320
Oh, then there's nothing to be done.

28:17.400 --> 28:19.840
- Sir, there's been an incident!
- What happened?

28:19.920 --> 28:22.160
There's a gun in the mediation room.

28:22.240 --> 28:23.720
- A gun during mediation?
- Let's go.

28:23.800 --> 28:25.480
- Oh, man, you guys are the pits!
- What will I do?

28:25.560 --> 28:27.040
[mother] Hey, someone, stop him!

28:27.120 --> 28:29.400
He's gone mad. He's lost the plot.

28:29.480 --> 28:30.680
[brother] I'm not gonna spare you!

28:30.760 --> 28:32.880
You don't know who I am,
what I'm capable of.

28:32.960 --> 28:35.360
[sings]

28:40.800 --> 28:42.520
[gasps] Nannu!

28:43.400 --> 28:44.400
[whimpers]

29:05.720 --> 29:07.000
[moans]

29:13.760 --> 29:15.440
[cop] Who brought a gun to court?

29:15.520 --> 29:16.520
Come out!

29:19.840 --> 29:22.240
[mother] Yeah, now he'll get the stick,

29:22.320 --> 29:24.960
crawling under the table
like a scared cockroach.

29:25.040 --> 29:26.400
[cop] Come out, out!

29:27.240 --> 29:28.760
You brought a gun to court?

29:28.840 --> 29:31.280
- [brother] Yeah, yeah. I'm coming out.
- Get up. Move!

29:31.360 --> 29:32.560
- Listen, I'm coming, okay?
- Move!

29:32.640 --> 29:33.920
[mother laughs]

29:34.000 --> 29:35.200
Stop dragging me.

29:35.280 --> 29:37.480
- Don't worry, we'll be fine.
- [brother] Don't you worry, Sonam.

29:37.560 --> 29:39.160
These guys don't know
who they're messing with.

29:40.720 --> 29:42.520
[chuckles] Sujata madam,

29:42.600 --> 29:45.280
I got him to pull out his gun, didn't I?

29:45.360 --> 29:47.200
- Now we'll get the divorce, right?
- [Sujata chuckles]

29:47.280 --> 29:49.520
- But you didn't get a beating, right?
- What?

29:49.600 --> 29:52.840
You should tie up your hair up
and let it down again, then you will.

29:52.920 --> 29:54.000
Will I?

29:55.360 --> 29:58.640
[cop 2] Today, Ghosh sir, passed an order
letting the lawyers take off their coats.

29:58.720 --> 30:01.080
So all the lawyers
were walking around in white shirts,

30:01.160 --> 30:04.520
that's when this man breached security
and got in without us realising it.

30:06.400 --> 30:07.760
We did the best we could, sir.

30:07.840 --> 30:10.120
- [phone chimes]
- I see. Very good.

30:08.000 --> 30:18.000
ভুয়া লিংক এড়িয়ে চলুন — অফিসিয়াল: -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

30:10.200 --> 30:12.320
[Sunil] We have the best facilities
here for our judges.

30:12.400 --> 30:13.800
You met our dear friend Shambhu,

30:13.880 --> 30:16.720
he's dressed as a monkey
to chase away the monkeys.

30:16.800 --> 30:18.760
I believe you met him at the corridor.

30:19.360 --> 30:22.160
- He extinguishes all kinds of fire.
- Check your messages.

30:22.240 --> 30:24.160
- Yes.
- Mr Tyagi?

30:24.240 --> 30:26.800
- I'll call you.
- Firearms in the court premises?

30:27.840 --> 30:29.840
If you expect me to suppress this matter--

30:29.920 --> 30:31.400
No, no! Why would you do that?

30:31.480 --> 30:34.640
On the contrary, in your letter,
this negligence must be added.

30:35.800 --> 30:37.240
Please. And question them.

30:37.320 --> 30:38.960
Look, Gosain is here.

30:39.040 --> 30:41.160
He was posted in that sector
at the time. Ask him.

30:41.240 --> 30:43.000
How did the gun get into the court?

30:43.080 --> 30:45.040
Sir, he came in wearing black pants
and a white shirt.

30:45.120 --> 30:46.560
So he got in without being checked.

30:46.640 --> 30:48.400
Without being checked? Why?

30:49.160 --> 30:50.440
[Gosain] We thought he was a lawyer.

30:50.520 --> 30:52.720
Of course,
lawyers always have their coats on.

30:52.800 --> 30:55.360
But today they took them off,
so we couldn't recognise him.

30:55.440 --> 30:57.120
Who allowed the lawyers
to take their coats off

30:57.200 --> 30:59.320
without understanding
the security implications?

30:59.400 --> 31:00.800
What's going on here?

31:00.880 --> 31:04.440
Sir, this sounds to me like it's
an act of negligence, nothing else.

31:04.520 --> 31:06.080
[Shubhkela] Are you sure, Vishwas?

31:06.160 --> 31:10.080
Then, uh, how did the gun pass
the metal detector?

31:10.160 --> 31:11.760
[Gosain] That hasn't been working, sir.

31:12.440 --> 31:14.920
And it was connected
to the transformer outside.

31:15.000 --> 31:18.400
Yes, sir, and the transformer broke down
during the heavy rain last week.

31:18.480 --> 31:20.120
I see.

31:20.880 --> 31:25.600
Sir, that means
it is not an act of negligence.

31:25.680 --> 31:27.880
- It's an act of--
- Act of God!

31:27.960 --> 31:31.920
You know, just like… [chuckles]
…getting electrocuted was an act of God.

31:32.000 --> 31:33.000
[Vishwas] Act of God.

31:33.640 --> 31:37.360
This gun getting into court
was also an act of God.

31:37.440 --> 31:39.000
Uh, but, Mr Ghosh,

31:39.560 --> 31:42.200
if two acts of God
take place on the same day,

31:42.920 --> 31:46.160
then, uh, will any
reasonable observer truly believe it?

31:46.240 --> 31:47.360
[Vishwas] That's true.

31:47.440 --> 31:51.760
Mr Tyagi, no matter how
reasonable the observer is,

31:52.720 --> 31:57.080
in this country,
he will never ever question God.

31:59.240 --> 32:00.680
- [chuckles]
- Bravo, sir.

32:03.400 --> 32:05.360
- Very true, sir. Thank you.
- Amazing, amazing.

32:19.200 --> 32:21.200
And what does this mean?

32:22.120 --> 32:24.520
- So, all set?
- Oh, ma'am, hi.

32:24.600 --> 32:25.600
Hi.

32:26.320 --> 32:27.960
Thank you, ma'am,
you really saved our marriage.

32:28.040 --> 32:29.040
- You're welcome.
- Yeah.

32:29.120 --> 32:31.160
And you even helped my brother. Thank you.

32:31.240 --> 32:33.360
You must let us know
if there's anything we can do for you.

32:33.440 --> 32:34.520
- Please.
- Okay.

32:34.600 --> 32:35.600
Be happy.

32:35.680 --> 32:36.680
Thank you.

32:37.960 --> 32:41.760
Sonam, uh, there is one thing you can do.

32:42.760 --> 32:44.760
- She sent you a voice note?
- No, man.

32:45.760 --> 32:47.200
Look, she didn't send a voice note, right?

32:47.280 --> 32:49.200
- No.
- Then she's screwing with you for sure.

32:49.280 --> 32:50.920
- So what do I do?
- Block that bitch!

32:51.600 --> 32:53.080
- You sure about that?
- 100%.

32:55.400 --> 32:56.400
\[chimes]

32:56.480 --> 32:57.720
It's a voice note.

32:59.520 --> 33:02.480
Hello, Mintu, sweety.

33:02.560 --> 33:05.360
- [laughs]
- [on phone] Hello, Mintu, sweety.

33:05.440 --> 33:06.720
Excuse me.

33:08.200 --> 33:11.080
- Hello, Mintu, sweety.
- [laughs]

33:11.160 --> 33:13.920
Hey, not here, not here.
Listen, is it her voice?

33:14.000 --> 33:17.040
- Hello, Mintu, sweety.
- Oh, wow! [chuckles]

33:18.440 --> 33:19.440
[sighs]

33:21.960 --> 33:24.480
- Varsha. Varsha.
- [laughs]

33:24.560 --> 33:25.800
I don't believe this.

33:38.920 --> 33:40.480
This is not the engagement ring is it?

33:40.560 --> 33:42.280
So you don't want it back, right?

33:42.360 --> 33:44.480
- [sucks teeth]
- No, tell me now. [chuckles]

33:44.560 --> 33:46.080
- Or you'll ask for it later.
- Crazy.

33:47.760 --> 33:48.760
[sighs]

33:49.960 --> 33:52.760
It's very sweet of you. Thank you.

33:55.520 --> 33:57.520
- Something to eat? [laughs]
- Sure. [laughs]

33:58.760 --> 33:59.840
[both] Cheers.

34:07.960 --> 34:09.560
- Are these Anand Snacks?
- Mmm.

34:10.200 --> 34:11.600
Was Mangesh's shut?

34:12.320 --> 34:13.320
[coughs]

34:24.960 --> 34:25.960
What?

34:31.560 --> 34:32.560
What are you doing?

34:33.720 --> 34:36.040
Hey, what are… [stammers]

34:36.120 --> 34:37.120
Hey, what's wrong?

34:37.720 --> 34:38.720
Varsha?

34:43.760 --> 34:45.320
- Good job.
- Thank you, sir.

34:45.400 --> 34:46.680
- [engine starts]
- [grunts]

34:49.360 --> 34:50.560
[both chuckle]

34:54.520 --> 34:56.400
[Shubhkela] Wow, hats off, Mr Tyagi.

34:56.480 --> 34:58.320
Ghosh sir's brought down some bigwigs.

34:58.400 --> 35:00.160
Now you've done the same to him.

35:01.200 --> 35:03.000
Luck is truly on your side.

35:03.720 --> 35:05.960
Who needs luck on one's side, Mr Kela?

35:07.240 --> 35:10.960
I have God's hand… on my head.

35:11.960 --> 35:13.960
May he guide all of us.

35:14.040 --> 35:15.200
[both laughing]

35:18.160 --> 35:20.440
[Shubhkela]
I need some luck on my side too.

35:20.520 --> 35:21.960
[laughing continues]
